                                  LTGOLD Q&A

                              1. PROGRAM CONCEPTS

         A. I  don't know Russian,  will I still be able to use LTGOLD
            to translate documents?

              The main problem with any electronic translation program
              is in  the  area  of  multiple  meaning  words.  Without
              knowledge of a language, the whole meaning of a sentence
              can be lost due to the use of a wrong noun or adjective.
              In  LTGOLD  we solved this problem by giving the English
              synonyms for the multiple meaning words.  An example  of
              this feature follows:

           Original English:

              "This new  file  formation  is written in Russian.  As a
         Russian file, it may be accessed on little or no notice. Your
         immediate attention is requested,  or we shall not be able to
         deliver the product before the end of fall. If the product is
         not delivered by this time, we can expect a fall in sales."

           Translated Russian:

         Electronically Translated by LTGOLD 2.0
         PART.REA PART.OUT                         Dec 28 10:04:43 1992


                                     ﾚﾄﾄﾄ The first form of the word
                                     ｳ           ﾚﾄﾄ the second form
                                     ｳ           ｳ
              ETO NOVOE FAJLOVOE FORMIROVANIE {1.STROJ}, NAPISANNOE NA
              RUSSKOM.  KAK RUSSKIJ FAJL ON  SMOJET  YNPABLYATJSYA  ZA
              MALENJKOE {2.KOROTKIJ} VREMYA ILI  VOOBSCE NE IZVESCENIE
              {3.ZAMECHATJ}.    VASHE    BEZOTLAGATELJNOE     VNIMANIE
              ZAPRASHIVAETSYA,  ILI  MY  NE  SMOJEM  POLUCHATJ PRODUKT
              PERED KONCOM  PADENIE   {4.OSENJ}.   ESLI   PRODUCT   NE
              DOSTAVLEN K  ETOMU  VREMENI,  MY  MOJEM  OJIDATJ PADENIE
              {5.OSENJ} PRODAJ.


         MULTIPLE MEANINGS:

          1 FORMATION:   TO MOLD - FORMIROVANIE,    TO LINE UP - STROJ
          2 LITTLE:      SIZE - MALENJKOE,          TIME - KOROTKIJ
          3 NOTICE:      PAPER - IZVESCENIE,        TO NOTICE - ZAMECHATJ
          4 FALL:        FALLING DOWN - PADENIE     TIME OF YR - OSENJ
          5 FALL:        FALLING DOWN - PADENIE     TIME OF YR - OSENJ


       PART.REA PART.OUT                          Dec 28 10:04:45 1992
       LINES: 10 CHARS: 369 WORDS: 57 FOUND: 57 (100) TIME 0:00:07
       CHARGE PER WORD: .10    AMOUNT PAYABLE: 5.70

              The completed  translated  text allows you to select the
              correct meaning of the word.  The  words  with  multiple
              meanings  are enclosed in brackets and numbered from the
              top to  bottom  of  each paragraph.  Each paragraph will
              have its own Multiple Meanings list.

                                    - 4 -
                                  LTGOLD Q&A

         B. I  am  a  professional  translator,  why  would  I  use an
            electronic translation program?

              One of  the  most time consuming tasks in translation is
              typing the text from English  to  Russian.  The  program
              does this for you and also allows you to modify the text
              on a sentence by sentence  basis.  Each  translator  has
              their  own  style  and LTGOLD is not intended to replace
              this style but to enhance it.

         C. I  am a professional translator and all I want the program
            for is to save me time in typing and  having  to  look  up
            complex  words and structures.  If I don't need all of the
            bells and whistles of LTGOLD what are my options?

              Along with LTGOLD we supply LTPRO.  LTPRO is a fast,  no
              frills version of LTGOLD. The translator puts all of the
              commands  in  one  line  and the program will create the
              translated output file. LTPRO also allows the Translator
              to  build  a  batch  file  that  could  include  several
              chapters or documents to be processed  without  operator
              intervention.  With  LTPRO  the  translator  is  able to
              design a batch file to translate thousands of  pages  of
              text  during  the night when the computer would normally
              be just collecting dust.

         D. What percentage can we expect to improve the time for  our
            translations through the use of LTGOLD?

              This depends totally on the workload of the translators.
              The programs should increase their productivity  by  80%
              or more.

         E. I  have documents that include charts and graphs that I do
            not want translated.  Is there a way to prevent  different
            parts from translation?

              Yes, a unique feature in LTGOLD allows you to put a stop
              and start translation code anywhere in the file. You may
              mark  a word,  phrase,  sentence or section (one or more
              paragraphs) not to be translated.

         F. I do not want my company name or product names translated.
            Is  there a way for me to install a list of words I always
            want left in English?

              Yes, the program includes a  file  called  "LTGOLD.IDS".
              This  file can be edited with any ASCII editor and looks
              at the way a word is written.  An example is the company
              NeXT. Anytime the program sees this word written in this
              format it will leave it in english.  If the program sees
              NEXT, Next, or next, it will be translated into Russian.







                                    - 5 -
                                  LTGOLD Q&A

         G. I  would  like  to  modify  the dictionaries supplied with
            LTGOLD. Can I do this?

              Yes, our product, LinguaTech Dictionaries (LTWORD), is a
              user friendly dictionary development tool.  It is a must
              for those who want to modify  existing  dictionaries  or
              create their own specific dictionaries.

         H. Why  don't  you  supply the LinguaTech Dictionary programs
            with LTGOLD?

              We found that most users do not have the qualified staff
              or time to develop dictionaries. Even though  LTWORD  is
              an easy program to  use, it  requires  a  good   working
              knowledge of both English and Russian to code words into
              their proper format.

         I.  I do not have the time or staff to code additional words.
             Is there a service available that can do this for me?

              Yes, we  offer  a  service  of  coding  both Russian and
              English words.  We  can  also  modify  the  distribution
              dictionaries  to  your  specific  needs.  For additional
              information on this subject please contact  your  dealer
              or distributor.

         J.  Most of my documents are related to a specific  industry.
             Are there  industry  specific  dictionaries available for
             translation of these documents?

              As with  any  specific area of interest such as medical,
              scientific,   biological,   military,   etc.   we   have
              dictionaries available or can develop them. If there are
              specific terms or words that are of interest we are able
              to code them into the specific dictionaries.

         K.  I like the BASIC dictionary but would like certain  words
             coded specifically  to  my  needs.  Is  there  a  service
             available to do this.

              Yes, we  are  able  to  modify the basic dictionaries to
              meet your specific needs.  When developing a  dictionary
              of  this  magnitude we must use the most generic meaning
              of a word as the primary form of translation and  always
              try to put multiple meanings with the basic meaning.














                                    - 6 -
                                  LTGOLD Q&A

                             2. FILES AND COMPUTER

         A. How  much disk space do I need on my hard drive to install
            LTGOLD?

              a minimum of 2.5 megabytes (free space 2,500,000 bytes).

         B. Do I need all of the files on my hard drive at all times?

              There are  four  dictionaries supplied with the program.
              The file  names  are  "BASE.DIC"  (main  English/Russian
              dictionary  and  should  always be present),  "BASE.RUS"
              (Russian  word  parameter  file  and  should  always  be
              present),  "COMPUTER.DIC"  (computer specific dictionary
              and does not need to  be  available  unless  translating
              computer   oriented   documents),   and   "BUSINESS.DIC"
              (business specific dictionary and does not  need  to  be
              available    unless    translating   business   oriented
              documents).

              This distribution also includes LinguaTech Pro  (LTPRO).
              If you do not want a command line translation version of
              LinguaTech Gold 2.0 on your system you may  remove  them
              for use later.

         C. I have a high density floppy drive that formats to over  2
            megabytes. Can I use this drive instead of my hard drive?

              The short answer is yes.  If you are interested in speed
              and  performance  the  hard  drive  is  always  the best
              option.

         D. My  computer  has  1024  Kb of main memory can the program
            utilize the difference between 640K and 1024K?

              Yes, Add  the  following  command to your CONFIG.SYS and
              the program will automatically use it:

              DEVICE=C:\DOS\SMARTDRV.SYS 320

         E. Will  LinguaTech Gold 2.0 conflict with my memory resident
            programs?

              Our experience   has   not   indicated  a  problem  with
              conflicts in this area.  It is impossible for us to  try
              all  memory  resident  programs  to  verify  this.  If a
              problem persists the first  suspect  is  usually  memory
              resident  programs.  Remove all memory resident programs
              and run the program.  If the problem goes away, add each
              memory  resident  program  back  one at a time until you
              find the culprit.








                                    - 7 -
                                  LTGOLD Q&A

         F. I have 2 megabytes of additional memory  installed  in  my
            computer.  Can the program use this memory and if so, what
            value is it.

              By installing the dictionaries in the additional  memory
              the  program will translate several hundred times faster
              than from the hard drive.

         G. What do I have to do to install the dictionaries into this
            additional memory.

              First of  all,  your  "CONFIG.SYS"  file  must  have the
              following commands:

         "DEVICE=C:\DOC\HIMEM.SYS"
                            ﾀ installs the DOS high memory driver

         "DEVICE=C:\DOS\RAMDRIVE.SYS 2048 /E"
                                           ﾀ Creates drive "E:" from the
                                             high memory

              NOTE: The  two  above  examples  assume  that  the files
                    "HIMEM.SYS"  and  "RAMDRIVE.SYS"  are  located  on
                    drive C: in the Subdirectory "DOS".

              You can  now  copy  the ".DIC" and ".RUS" files to drive
              E:. The command to start LTGOLD should read:

                   ﾚﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄ Changes your default subdirectory to LTGOLD
          "CD\LTGOLD"
          "LTGOLD -D E:"
                   ﾀﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄ Tells the program your dictionaries  are on
                           your E: drive

         H. When  I  run LTGOLD I get some letters that are garbled on
            the screen.

              This is  due  to the lack of a Cyrillic (Russian) screen
              driver. Run "RKVGA.COM" before running LTGOLD.

              The command should look like the following:

              RKVGA/h
                    ﾀﾄ font
              To remove the driver type:

              RKVGA/k
                    ﾀﾄ kill the driver

         I. I  have  a laptop and RKVGA does not work where I have the
            cursor. Is this a problem with LTGOLD?

              The problem is not with LTGOLD.  It is with the type  of
              screen   you   have.   To  correct  this  problem,  most
              manufacturers have included programs to change the  type
              of  screen  emulation.  Try the different modes supplied
              (MGA, CGA, EGA, and VGA). One of these modes should work
              with the Cyrillic screen driver.

                                    - 8 -
                                  LTGOLD Q&A

         J.  Does  LTGOLD  or  the other LinguaTech programs require a
             key disk or an electronic device  to  allow  them  to  be
             used.

              No, We  feel  that  this   is   unnecessary   and   very
              destructive  to  the  legitimate  user.  The reason that
              other companies use to explain the use of these  devices
              is  to  protect their software rights.  They do not look
              past their own needs when  subjecting  a  user  to  such
              brutal  tactics.  Here  are  the  negatives  of  the two
              different forms of  protection  used  by  some  software
              companies:

              Key Disk:

              A key disk  is  a  floppy  diskette  that  the  software
              requires  to  be  in  the floppy drive at the startup or
              during the running of the program.

              a. Key Disks are not able to be copied by most users. If
                 the  Key  Disk is destroyed for any reason you are no
                 longer able to use the program until the manufacturer
                 replaces  it.  This  is on a level of having to go to
                 the car dealer every time you need gasoline for  your
                 car.

              b. The  "key  disk"  is  a  problem  for users of laptop
                 computers. Most run on battery and when accessing the
                 floppy  drive  more  power  is  consumed.  They  also
                 prevent the user  from  translating  a  file  on  the
                 floppy drive as the key disk must always be in place.
                 Again, this defeats the reason for having a laptop if
                 the key disk develops a problem.

              c. Most  key  disks come in either 3.5" or 5.25" format.
                 If the wrong size is shipped with the program or  you
                 replace  your  computer  you  must  go  back  to  the
                 software company for a replacement.

              d. Most programs that require a key  disk  also  require
                 you  to reboot the computer once you stop running the
                 program.  This   is   very   inconvenient   for   the
                 professional  or  business user who has to accomplish
                 multiple tasks.

              Electronic Key:

              An Electronic  Key  is  a  device  that  connects to the
              serial or parallel port of your computer. If this device
              is not always present the program will not operate.

              a. A   major  problem  reported  with  these  electronic
                 devices is  their  reliability.  Several  users  have
                 reported   damage  to  their  computers  due  to  bad
                 manufacturing or design.




                                    - 9 -
                                  LTGOLD Q&A

              b. Some smaller laptops do not have serial  or  parallel
                 ports unless an external interface is connected. This
                 requires additional  hardware  and  expense  for  the
                 user.

              c. Some  printers will not function correctly with these
                 devices connected.

              e. There are some very fast,  reliable,  and  productive
                 backup  programs  that  find  a  conflict  when these
                 devices are connected.

              We feel both of these schemes also add to  the  cost  of
              the  product  and  are passed on to the legitimate user.
              They are easily  defeated  by  those  with  the  correct
              knowledge and the desire to illegally copy the programs.

              It is our policy to design products around our users. If
              we do not trust our users,  we can not  expect  them  to
              trust and believe in us.  Our distribution diskettes are
              easily copied with  DISKCOPY  (DOS  program).  The  only
              protection  we  include  is  designed for the user.  Our
              protection requires the user to put their unique  serial
              number into the program when they are installing it. The
              main reason for this is to make sure that the user knows
              their  serial number and that the program is stamped for
              easier  trouble  shooting.  The  Install  program   also
              verifies all of the options in the computer to allow the
              programs to run more efficiently.






























