                                  LTGOLD Q&A

                                 3. LTGOLD PROGRAM

         A. I  would  like  to  always install the business dictionary
            when I start the program.  Is there a command to allow  me
            to do this?

              Yes, when you start LTGOLD,  we allow several  different
              options  or  defaults  to  be present.  To automatically
              install the business dictionary your command to run  the
              program should read:

              LTGOLD -c b
                        ﾀﾄﾄﾄﾄ business.dic

         B. I want to install all of the dictionaries when I start the
            program. Is there a simple way to do this?

              Yes, as  in  item  3A,  you  may define the options when
              starting the program. To install all of the dictionaries
              your command line should read:

              LTGOLD -c bcu
                        ｳｳﾀﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄ user.dic (4th .dic)
                        ｳﾀﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄ computer.dic (3rd .dic)
                        ﾀﾄﾄﾄﾄ business.dic (2nd .dic)


              The priority  order  is  defined by where you instal the
              dictionary in the command line.   BASE.DIC is always #1.

         C. I  would  like to have the computer or business dictionary
            before the basic dictionary. Is this possible?

              Yes, it is possible but not recommended. It is important
              to remember that the basic dictionary (BASE.DIC) has the
              basic  forms  of  words  required  for the high level of
              translation provided by LTGOLD.  We can not  assume  any
              responsibility  for  the effects this could have on your
              translations.

         D. I use Word Perfect and Wordstar as my word processors. Can
            LTGOLD translate documents from these programs?

              Yes, most  word  processors  allow  you to convert their
              format to an ASCII format.  It  is  usually  called  the
              "document"  mode.  Export  the  document created by your
              word processor as an  ASCII  file,  process  it  through
              LTGOLD, bring it back into your word processor.











                                    - 11 -
                                  LTGOLD Q&A


         E. My word processor does not work with Cyrillics. Is there a
            way to modify it to do so?


              Most word  processors  are  now   available   from   the
              manufacturer  in a Cyrillic format.  Contact your dealer
              or the manufacturer  for  further  information  on  this
              subject. Use caution to make sure that you only purchase
              a  manufacturer  modified  product.   Several   versions
              available  have  been  modified by unethical parties for
              the purpose of spreading viruses.


         F. I  would  like  to  work  with  LTGOLD from within my word
            processor. Is this possible?


              Some word  processors  allow  interaction  between other
              programs.  This is accomplished through a command called
              "macros".  The  LTGOLD  distribution  disk  includes the
              macros for WORD 5.0, 5.5 WINWORD 2.0, and MultiEdit. For 
              other  word   processors,  please  contact  your  dealer  
              or distributor.


         G. I do not have an editor that works with Cyrillics.  How do
            I edit Russian text created by LTGOLD?


              LTGOLD has  a  built in editor.  It is simple to use and
              allows the user to produce a finished product.


         H. When I process a file through  LTGOLD  I  have  additional
            text  on  the top and the bottom of the document.  What is
            this for?


              Several professional translators pointed out  that  they
              had  trouble  keeping  track  of  when they translated a
              document and which version  they  were  working  on.  We
              included  the following text to assist with the document
              information:


